*pam-0.78-r4 (06 Sep 2007)

  06 Sep 2007; EADS D&S <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  pam-0.78-r4.ebuild, +files/pam-°.78-core-passwd.patch:
  /etc is read-only, /etc/core is now read-write
  Modify passwd file in /etc/core instead of /etc.
  Modify the lock file too (no longer in /etc/.pwd.lock).

  25 Aug 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  -files/pam.d.clip/*:
  Ah well, actually remove those files, which will be provided by
  sys-apps/shadow (which provides conflicting versions otherwise).

*pam-0.78-r3 (24 Aug 2006)

  24 Aug 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  pam-0.78-r3.ebuild, +files/pam.d.clip/*:
  Initial clip import, add IUSE clip that installs a pam_mount
  compliant system-auth in pam.d. That used to be installed by 
  sys-auth/pam_mount, creating a conflict with pam.
